{{infobox Organization |name = Luxembourg Amateur Radio Union |image = LARU_logo_2014.gif |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = LARU |motto = |formation = |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit organization]] |status = |purpose = Science, Education |headquarters = |location = [[Luxembourg]] |region_served = [[Luxembourg]] |membership = |language = [[Luxembourgish language|Luxembourgish]], [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]], [[English language|English]] |leader_title = President |leader_name = Marc Storck LX1DUC |main_organ = |affiliations = |num_staff = |budget = |website = http://www.laru.lu/ |remarks = }}
The '''Luxembourg Amateur Radio Union''' (LARU) (in [[German language|German]], Luxemburger Amateur Radio Union, in [[French language|French]], Union des Radioamateurs du Luxembourg) is a national [[non-profit organization]] for [[amateur radio]] enthusiasts in [[Luxembourg]]<ref name="Amateur-Radio-Organizations">Amateur Radio Organizations. [[List of amateur radio organizations]].</ref> .<ref name="LARU-webpage">Webpage of the LARU [http://laru.lu/] http://laru.lu. Retrieved Apr. 2, 2015.</ref> The LARU was founded in January 1, 2014. The LARU promotes technical progress and cohesion of amateur radio operators. The LARU sets priorities in emergency communications, digital voice communications, digital data transmission, [[science]] and [[education]].<ref name="LARU-foundation">Foundation of the LARU [http://laru.lu/laru/our-mission.html]. Retrieved Dec. 30, 2014.</ref>
The LARU offers workshops dedicated to [[amateur radio]], offers a radio course for the preparation of the amateur radio exam ([[HAREC]] and [[NOVICE]]), organises fielddays and [[Amateur radio|ham]]-meetings, operates voice repeaters, [[Automatic Packet Reporting System|APRS]] [[digipeater]]s, servers and gateways, activates special callsigns. The organization operates webpages dedicated to emergency communications <ref name="EMCOMM.SERVICES">Luxembourgish web presence dedicated to emergency communications [http://emcomm.services] http://emcomm.services. Retrieved Dec. 30, 2014.</ref> and [[Digital mobile radio|DMR]] an open digital radio standard for professional mobile radio used in [[amateur radio]] .<ref name="HAM-DMR.LU">Luxembourgish web presence dedicated to [[Digital mobile radio|DMR]] [http://www.ham-dmr.lu] http://ham-dmr.lu. Retrieved Dec. 30, 2014.</ref> The amateur radio club callsign of the LARU is LX9LARU.<ref name="LARU-webpage">Webpage of the LARU [http://laru.lu/] http://laru.lu. Retrieved Apr. 2, 2015.</ref> The LARU also uses the call LX4E for emergency operations and other special activities.<ref name="LARU-CALLBOOK">Callbook of the LARU [http://laru.lu/laru/callbook.html] http://laru.lu/laru/callbook.html. Retrieved May. 13, 2015.</ref>
The LARU also operates the LARU LX QSL Bureau.<ref name="LARU-LX-QSL-Bureau">Webpage of the LARU LX QSL Bureau [http://qsl.lu] http://qsl.lu. Retrieved Jul. 18, 2014.</ref> Herewith the LARU supports [[amateur radio operator]]s in Luxembourg and in the world by promoting the exchange of [[QSL card]]s.
Although the LARU is a national amateur radio organization representing the interests of amateur radio operators in Luxembourg, it is not a member of the [[International Amateur Radio Union|IARU]] because IARU rules don't allow a membership.<ref name="iaru">International Amateur Radio Union. [http://www.iaru.org/iaru-soc.html "Member Societies"].Retrieved Dec. 30, 2014.</ref>
== Amateur radio repeaters operated by the LARU == {{As of|2017}} the LARU operates 4 [[Digital mobile radio|DMR]] repeaters and 2 [[Automatic Packet Reporting System|APRS]] repeaters.<ref name="LARU-APRS">APRS repeaters operated by LARU [http://laru.lu/on-the-air/lx-repeaters.html] Retrieved Dec. 24, 2017.</ref>
